chunk: Izidor Maklary is a Budapest-based software developer with a background in joinery and CNC programming.
He transitioned from joinery to programming, valuing smooth workflows, consistency, and planning.
Izidor's main technical skills include TypeScript, Node.js, and developing Cloudflare Workers.
He started his developer career in 2022 and enjoys exploring new technologies.
Izidor is also a hobby producer, cyclist, and table tennis player with a passion for arts and contemporary music.
He values learning about different cultures through travel.
Izidor's portfolio project features a simple navigation panel and an AI chatbot for tailored summaries.
He used Vercel's tooling and Next.js for the portfolio's frontend and API.
The portfolio's content is managed in Notion and queried via notion-sdk-js.
Izidor integrated OpenAI APIs to handle AI tasks, ensuring scalability and accurate responses.
His portfolio showcases his learnings and serves as a demonstration of his skills.
Izidor's web development journey began with a 7-month bootcamp at Becode Antwerp.
The bootcamp emphasized teamwork, self-guided learning, and effective question formulation.
Izidor spent his early developer years with Bubbly-Doo, working on global scale projects.
At Bubbly-Doo, he gained experience with TypeScript on both frontend and backend.
He worked with cutting-edge technologies and contributed to the open-source community.
Izidor's internship at Bubbly-Doo involved creating a GraphQL API and dashboard.
He learned about objection (Knex-based ORM), Express.js, and AWS/Lambda setups.
Izidor created a shared logic layer to avoid code duplication between APIs.
He implemented GraphQL subscriptions in a serverless environment using AWS/Lambda and DynamoDB.
Izidor and Hans Otto developed a package for faster GraphQL subscription handling with durable objects.
The improved setup resulted in almost instantaneous dashboard updates.
Izidor developed Bubbly-Doo's internal dashboard using Next.js and Apollo Client.
The dashboard features scroll-based pagination for efficient order management.
He added support for batch operations and robust filtering to handle large order volumes.
The dashboard remains in use, providing valuable service to users.
Izidor integrated with 11 printing partners globally over nearly 4 years.
He set up Cloudflare Workers for order placement and AWS/Lambda for status updates.
